<dl id="n15069c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15069c">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15069c"> 69(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> vengeance is / mine</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&ldquo;Obsessive Acts and Religious Practices&rdquo; (1907)]</font>: A progressive renunciation of inherent instincts, the satisfaction of which is capable of giving direct pleasure to the ego, appears to be one of the foundations of human civilization. Some part of this repression is effected by means of the various religions, in that they require individuals to sacrifice the satisfaction of their instincts to the divinity. &lsquo;<mark>Vengeance is mine</mark>, saith the Lord.&rsquo; <small> Sigmund Freud, <a name="SFCP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SFCP"><cite title="source">Collected Papers II</cite></a> (1924) 34</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15245c" href="c15all.htm#c15245c">VI.C.15:245(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
